</div>


<h1>Online Bible: New World Translation of the Holy Scriptures</h1>
</noscript>
<p class="title">2 Kings 9:1-37</p>
<form class="formtext">
<input type="hidden" name="chapterCount" value="25">
<input type="hidden" name="verseCount" value="37">
<p><a name="bk1" class="vsAnchor">1</a>
       <span id="vs1">And E&middot;li&acute;sha the prophet, for his part, called one of the sons of the prophets and then said to him: “Gird up your loins and take this flask of oil in your hand and go to Ra&acute;moth-gil&acute;e&middot;ad.</span> <a name="bk2" class="vsAnchor">2</a>
       <span id="vs2">When you have come in there, see Je&acute;hu the son of Je&middot;hosh&acute;a&middot;phat the son of Nim&acute;shi there; and you must come in and make him get up from the midst of his brothers and bring him into the innermost chamber.</span> <a name="bk3" class="vsAnchor">3</a>
       <span id="vs3">And you must take the flask of oil and pour it out upon his head and say, ‘This is what Jehovah has said: “I do anoint you as king over Israel.”’ And you must open the door and flee and not wait.”</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk4" class="vsAnchor">4</a>
       <span id="vs4">And the attendant, the prophet’s attendant, got on his way to Ra&acute;moth-gil&acute;e&middot;ad.</span> <a name="bk5" class="vsAnchor">5</a>
       <span id="vs5">When he came in, why, there the chiefs of the military force were seated. He now said: “There is a word I have for you, O chief.” At this Je&acute;hu said: “For which one of all of us?” Then he said: “For you, O chief.”</span> <a name="bk6" class="vsAnchor">6</a>
       <span id="vs6">So he got up and came into the house; and he proceeded to pour the oil out upon his head and say to him: “This is what Jehovah the God of Israel has said, ‘I do anoint you as king over Jehovah’s people, that is, over Israel.</span> <a name="bk7" class="vsAnchor">7</a>
       <span id="vs7">And you must strike down the house of A&acute;hab your lord, and I must avenge the blood of my servants the prophets and the blood of all the servants of Jehovah at the hand of Jez&acute;e&middot;bel.</span> <a name="bk8" class="vsAnchor">8</a>
       <span id="vs8">And the whole house of A&acute;hab must perish; and I must cut off from A&acute;hab anyone urinating against a wall and any helpless and worthless one in Israel.</span> <a name="bk9" class="vsAnchor">9</a>
       <span id="vs9">And I must constitute the house of A&acute;hab like the house of Jer&middot;o&middot;bo&acute;am the son of Ne&acute;bat and like the house of Ba&acute;a&middot;sha the son of A&middot;hi&acute;jah.</span> <a name="bk10" class="vsAnchor">10</a>
       <span id="vs10">And Jez&acute;e&middot;bel the dogs will eat up in the tract of land at Jez&acute;re&middot;el, and there will be no one burying her.’” With that he opened the door and went fleeing.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk11" class="vsAnchor">11</a>
       <span id="vs11">As for Je&acute;hu, he went out to the servants of his lord, and they began to say to him: “Is everything all right? Why did this crazy man come in to you?” But he said to them: “Y<span class="smallcaps">OU</span> yourselves well know the man and his sort of talk.”</span> <a name="bk12" class="vsAnchor">12</a>
       <span id="vs12">But they said: “It is false! Tell us, please.” Then he said: “It was like this and like that that he talked to me, saying, ‘This is what Jehovah has said: “I do anoint you as king over Israel.”’”</span> <a name="bk13" class="vsAnchor">13</a>
       <span id="vs13">At this they hurriedly took each one his garment and put it under him upon the bare steps, and they began to blow the horn and say: “Je&acute;hu has become king!”</span> <a name="bk14" class="vsAnchor">14</a>
       <span id="vs14">And Je&acute;hu the son of Je&middot;hosh&acute;a&middot;phat the son of Nim&acute;shi proceeded to conspire against Je&middot;ho&acute;ram.</span>
</p>

<p> 
       <span id="vs14-2">And Je&middot;ho&acute;ram himself had happened to be keeping guard at Ra&acute;moth-gil&acute;e&middot;ad, he with all Israel, because of Haz&acute;a&middot;el the king of Syria.</span> <a name="bk15" class="vsAnchor">15</a>
       <span id="vs15">Later Je&middot;ho&acute;ram the king returned to get healed at Jez&acute;re&middot;el from the wounds that the Syrians got to inflict upon him when he fought Haz&acute;a&middot;el the king of Syria.</span>
</p>

<p> 
       <span id="vs15-2">Je&acute;hu now said: “If <span class="smallcaps">YOUR</span> soul agrees, do not let anyone go out in escape from the city to go and make report in Jez&acute;re&middot;el.”</span> <a name="bk16" class="vsAnchor">16</a>
       <span id="vs16">And Je&acute;hu began to ride and go to Jez&acute;re&middot;el; for Je&middot;ho&acute;ram was lying there, and A&middot;ha&middot;zi&acute;ah the king of Judah himself had gone down to see Je&middot;ho&acute;ram.</span> <a name="bk17" class="vsAnchor">17</a>
       <span id="vs17">And the watchman was standing upon the tower in Jez&acute;re&middot;el, and he got to see the heaving mass of Je&acute;hu’s [men] as he was coming, and he at once said: “There is a heaving mass [of men] that I am seeing.” At that Je&middot;ho&acute;ram said: “Take a cavalryman and send him to meet them, and let him say, ‘Is there peace?’”</span> <a name="bk18" class="vsAnchor">18</a>
       <span id="vs18">Accordingly a rider on a horse went to meet him and said: “This is what the king has said, ‘Is there peace?’” But Je&acute;hu said: “What do you have to do with ‘peace’? Get around to my rear!”</span>
</p>

<p> 
       <span id="vs18-2">And the watchman went on to report, saying: “The messenger came as far as to them, but he has not returned.”</span> <a name="bk19" class="vsAnchor">19</a>
       <span id="vs19">So he sent out a second rider on a horse, who, when he came to them, proceeded to say: “This is what the king has said, ‘Is there peace?’” But Je&acute;hu said: “What do you have to do with ‘peace’? Get around to my rear!”</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk20" class="vsAnchor">20</a>
       <span id="vs20">And the watchman went on to report, saying: “He came as far as to them, but he has not returned; and the driving is like the driving of Je&acute;hu the grandson of Nim&acute;shi, for it is with madness that he drives.”</span> <a name="bk21" class="vsAnchor">21</a>
       <span id="vs21">At that Je&middot;ho&acute;ram said: “Hitch up!” So his war chariot was hitched up and Je&middot;ho&acute;ram the king of Israel and A&middot;ha&middot;zi&acute;ah the king of Judah went out, each in his own war chariot. As they continued on out to meet Je&acute;hu, they got to find him in the tract of land of Na&acute;both the Jez&acute;re&middot;el&middot;ite.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk22" class="vsAnchor">22</a>
       <span id="vs22">And it came about that as soon as Je&middot;ho&acute;ram saw Je&acute;hu, he immediately said: “Is there peace, Je&acute;hu?” But he said: “What peace could there be as long as there are the fornications of Jez&acute;e&middot;bel your mother and her many sorceries?”</span> <a name="bk23" class="vsAnchor">23</a>
       <span id="vs23">At once Je&middot;ho&acute;ram made a turn with his hands, that he might flee, and said to A&middot;ha&middot;zi&acute;ah: “There is trickery, A&middot;ha&middot;zi&acute;ah!”</span> <a name="bk24" class="vsAnchor">24</a>
       <span id="vs24">And Je&acute;hu himself filled his hand with a bow and proceeded to shoot Je&middot;ho&acute;ram between the arms, so that the arrow came out at his heart, and he collapsed in his war chariot.</span> <a name="bk25" class="vsAnchor">25</a>
       <span id="vs25">He now said to Bid&acute;kar his adjutant: “Lift him up; throw him into the tract of the field of Na&acute;both the Jez&acute;re&middot;el&middot;ite; for remember: I and you were riding teams behind A&acute;hab his father, and Jehovah himself lifted up this pronouncement against him:</span> <a name="bk26" class="vsAnchor">26</a>
       <span id="vs26">‘“Certainly the blood of Na&acute;both and the blood of his sons I saw yesterday,” is the utterance of Jehovah, “and I shall certainly repay you in this tract of land,” is the utterance of Jehovah.’ So now, lift him up; throw him into the tract of land according to the word of Jehovah.”</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk27" class="vsAnchor">27</a>
       <span id="vs27">And A&middot;ha&middot;zi&acute;ah the king of Judah himself saw it and took to flight by the way of the garden house. (Later Je&acute;hu went in pursuit of him and said: “Him also! S<span class="smallcaps">TRIKE</span> him down!” So they struck him down while in the chariot on the way up to Gur, which is by Ib&acute;le&middot;am. And he continued his flight to Me&middot;gid&acute;do and got to die there.</span> <a name="bk28" class="vsAnchor">28</a>
       <span id="vs28">Then his servants carried him in a chariot to Jerusalem, and so they buried him in his grave with his forefathers in the City of David.</span> <a name="bk29" class="vsAnchor">29</a>
       <span id="vs29">And it was in the eleventh year of Je&middot;ho&acute;ram the son of A&acute;hab that A&middot;ha&middot;zi&acute;ah had become king over Judah.)</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk30" class="vsAnchor">30</a>
       <span id="vs30">At length Je&acute;hu came to Jez&acute;re&middot;el, and Jez&acute;e&middot;bel herself heard of it. And she proceeded to paint her eyes with black paint and do her head up beautifully and to look down through the window.</span> <a name="bk31" class="vsAnchor">31</a>
       <span id="vs31">And Je&acute;hu himself came in by the gate. She now said: “Did it go all right with Zim&acute;ri the killer of his lord?”</span> <a name="bk32" class="vsAnchor">32</a>
       <span id="vs32">At that he raised his face toward the window and said: “Who is with me? Who?” Immediately two or three court officials looked down at him.</span> <a name="bk33" class="vsAnchor">33</a>
       <span id="vs33">So he said: “Let her drop!” Then they let her drop, and some of her blood went spattering upon the wall and upon the horses; and he now trampled upon her.</span> <a name="bk34" class="vsAnchor">34</a>
       <span id="vs34">After that he came on in and ate and drank and then said: “Y<span class="smallcaps">OU</span> men, please, take care of this accursed one and bury her, for she is the daughter of a king.”</span> <a name="bk35" class="vsAnchor">35</a>
       <span id="vs35">When they went to bury her, they did not find anything of her but the skull and the feet and the palms of the hands.</span> <a name="bk36" class="vsAnchor">36</a>
       <span id="vs36">When they returned and told him, he went on to say: “It is the word of Jehovah that he spoke by means of his servant E&middot;li&acute;jah the Tish&acute;bite, saying, ‘In the tract of land of Jez&acute;re&middot;el the dogs will eat the flesh of Jez&acute;e&middot;bel.</span> <a name="bk37" class="vsAnchor">37</a>
       <span id="vs37">And the dead body of Jez&acute;e&middot;bel will certainly become as manure upon the face of the field in the tract of land of Jez&acute;re&middot;el, that they may not say: “This is Jez&acute;e&middot;bel.”’”</span>
</p>
</form>

