<h1>Online Bible: New World Translation of the Holy Scriptures</h1>
</noscript>
<p class="title">2 Kings 10:1-36</p>
<form class="formtext">
<input type="hidden" name="chapterCount" value="25">
<input type="hidden" name="verseCount" value="36">
<p><a name="bk1" class="vsAnchor">1</a>
       <span id="vs1">Now A&acute;hab had seventy sons in Sa&middot;mar&acute;i&middot;a. Therefore Je&acute;hu wrote letters and sent them to Sa&middot;mar&acute;i&middot;a to the princes of Jez&acute;re&middot;el, the older men and the caretakers of A&acute;hab, saying:</span> <a name="bk2" class="vsAnchor">2</a>
       <span id="vs2">“Now, then, at the very time that this letter comes to <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> there are with <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> the sons of <span class="smallcaps">YOUR</span> lord, and there are with <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> the war chariots and the horses and a fortified city and the armor.</span> <a name="bk3" class="vsAnchor">3</a>
       <span id="vs3">And <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> must see which is the best and most upright of the sons of <span class="smallcaps">YOUR</span> lord and put him upon the throne of his father. Then fight for the house of <span class="smallcaps">YOUR</span> lord.”</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk4" class="vsAnchor">4</a>
       <span id="vs4">And they became very greatly afraid and began to say: “Look! Two kings themselves did not stand before him, and how shall we ourselves stand?”</span> <a name="bk5" class="vsAnchor">5</a>
       <span id="vs5">Consequently the one who was over the house and the one who was over the city and the older men and the caretakers sent to Je&acute;hu, saying: “We are your servants, and everything that you say to us we shall do. We shall not make anyone king. What is good in your own eyes do.”</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk6" class="vsAnchor">6</a>
       <span id="vs6">At that he wrote them a second letter, saying: “If <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> belong to me, and it is my voice that <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> are obeying, take the heads of the men that are sons of <span class="smallcaps">YOUR</span> lord and come to me tomorrow at this time at Jez&acute;re&middot;el.”</span>
</p>

<p> 
       <span id="vs6-2">Now the sons of the king, seventy men, were with the distinguished men of the city that were bringing them up.</span> <a name="bk7" class="vsAnchor">7</a>
       <span id="vs7">And it came about that as soon as the letter came to them, they went taking the sons of the king and slaughtering [them], seventy men, after which they put their heads in baskets and sent them to him at Jez&acute;re&middot;el.</span> <a name="bk8" class="vsAnchor">8</a>
       <span id="vs8">Then the messenger came in and told him, saying: “They have brought the heads of the sons of the king.” So he said: “P<span class="smallcaps">UT</span> them in two heaps at the entrance of the gate until morning.”</span> <a name="bk9" class="vsAnchor">9</a>
       <span id="vs9">And it came about in the morning that he proceeded to go out. Then he stood still and said to all the people: “Y<span class="smallcaps">OU</span> are righteous. Here I myself conspired against my lord, and I got to kill him; but who struck down all these?</span> <a name="bk10" class="vsAnchor">10</a>
       <span id="vs10">Know, then, that nothing of Jehovah’s word will fall [unfulfilled] to the earth that Jehovah has spoken against the house of A&acute;hab; and Jehovah himself has done what he spoke by means of his servant E&middot;li&acute;jah.”</span> <a name="bk11" class="vsAnchor">11</a>
       <span id="vs11">Moreover, Je&acute;hu went on to strike down all who were left over of the house of A&acute;hab in Jez&acute;re&middot;el and all his distinguished men and his acquaintances and his priests, until he had let no survivor of his remain.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk12" class="vsAnchor">12</a>
       <span id="vs12">And he proceeded to rise and come in, then get on his way to Sa&middot;mar&acute;i&middot;a. The binding house of the shepherds was on the way.</span> <a name="bk13" class="vsAnchor">13</a>
       <span id="vs13">And Je&acute;hu himself encountered the brothers of A&middot;ha&middot;zi&acute;ah the king of Judah. When he said to them, “Who are <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span>?” then they said: “We are the brothers of A&middot;ha&middot;zi&acute;ah, and we are on our way down to ask if all is well with the sons of the king and the sons of the lady.”</span> <a name="bk14" class="vsAnchor">14</a>
       <span id="vs14">Immediately he said: “Seize them alive, <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> men!” So they seized them alive and slaughtered them at the cistern of the binding house, forty-two men, and he did not let a single one of them remain.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk15" class="vsAnchor">15</a>
       <span id="vs15">As he was going along from there he got to encounter Je&middot;hon&acute;a&middot;dab the son of Re&acute;chab [coming] to meet him. When he blessed him, he accordingly said to him: “Is your heart upright with me, just as my own heart is with your heart?”</span>
</p>

<p> 
       <span id="vs15-2">To this Je&middot;hon&acute;a&middot;dab said: “It is.”</span>
</p>

<p> 
       <span id="vs15-3">“If it is, do give me your hand.”</span>
</p>

<p> 
       <span id="vs15-4">So he gave him his hand. At that he made him get up into the chariot with him.</span> <a name="bk16" class="vsAnchor">16</a>
       <span id="vs16">Then he said: “Do go along with me and look upon my toleration of no rivalry toward Jehovah.” And they kept him riding with him in his war chariot.</span> <a name="bk17" class="vsAnchor">17</a>
       <span id="vs17">Finally he came to Sa&middot;mar&acute;i&middot;a. Now he went striking down all who were left over of A&acute;hab’s in Sa&middot;mar&acute;i&middot;a, until he had annihilated them, according to Jehovah’s word that he had spoken to E&middot;li&acute;jah.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk18" class="vsAnchor">18</a>
       <span id="vs18">Further, Je&acute;hu collected all the people together and said to them: “A&acute;hab, on the one hand, worshiped Ba&acute;al a little. Je&acute;hu, on the other hand, will worship him a great deal.</span> <a name="bk19" class="vsAnchor">19</a>
       <span id="vs19">So now call all the prophets of Ba&acute;al, all his worshipers and all his priests to me. Do not let a single one be missing, because I have a great sacrifice for Ba&acute;al. Anyone that is missing will not keep living.” As for Je&acute;hu, he acted slyly, for the purpose of destroying the worshipers of Ba&acute;al.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk20" class="vsAnchor">20</a>
       <span id="vs20">And Je&acute;hu went on to say: “Sanctify a solemn assembly for Ba&acute;al.” Accordingly they proclaimed it.</span> <a name="bk21" class="vsAnchor">21</a>
       <span id="vs21">After that Je&acute;hu sent through all Israel, so that all the worshipers of Ba&acute;al came in. And not a single one was left over that did not come in. And they kept coming into the house of Ba&acute;al, and the house of Ba&acute;al came to be full from end to end.</span> <a name="bk22" class="vsAnchor">22</a>
       <span id="vs22">He now said to the one who was over the wardrobe: “Bring out garments for all the worshipers of Ba&acute;al.” So he brought the attire out for them.</span> <a name="bk23" class="vsAnchor">23</a>
       <span id="vs23">Then Je&acute;hu entered with Je&middot;hon&acute;a&middot;dab the son of Re&acute;chab into the house of Ba&acute;al. He now said to the worshipers of Ba&acute;al: “Search carefully and see that there may be here with <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> none of the worshipers of Jehovah, but only the worshipers of Ba&acute;al.”</span> <a name="bk24" class="vsAnchor">24</a>
       <span id="vs24">Finally they came in to render up sacrifices and burnt offerings, and Je&acute;hu himself stationed eighty men outside at his disposal and went on to say: “As for the man that escapes from the men whom I am bringing into <span class="smallcaps">YOUR</span> hands, the one’s soul will go for the other’s soul.”</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk25" class="vsAnchor">25</a>
       <span id="vs25">And it came about that as soon as he finished rendering up the burnt offering, Je&acute;hu immediately said to the runners and the adjutants: “Come in, strike them down! Do not let a single one go out.” And the runners and the adjutants began to strike them down with the edge of the sword and to throw them out, and they kept going as far as the city of the house of Ba&acute;al.</span> <a name="bk26" class="vsAnchor">26</a>
       <span id="vs26">Then they brought out the sacred pillars of the house of Ba&acute;al and burned each one.</span> <a name="bk27" class="vsAnchor">27</a>
       <span id="vs27">Further, they pulled down the sacred pillar of Ba&acute;al and pulled down the house of Ba&acute;al, and they kept it set aside for privies down to this day.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk28" class="vsAnchor">28</a>
       <span id="vs28">Thus Je&acute;hu annihilated Ba&acute;al out of Israel.</span> <a name="bk29" class="vsAnchor">29</a>
       <span id="vs29">It was only the sins of Jer&middot;o&middot;bo&acute;am the son of Ne&acute;bat, with which he caused Israel to sin, that Je&acute;hu did not turn aside from following them, [that is,] the golden calves of which one was in Beth&acute;el and one in Dan.</span> <a name="bk30" class="vsAnchor">30</a>
       <span id="vs30">Consequently Jehovah said to Je&acute;hu: “For the reason that you have acted well in doing what is right in my eyes, [and] according to all that was in my heart you have done to the house of A&acute;hab, sons themselves to the fourth generation will sit for you upon the throne of Israel.”</span> <a name="bk31" class="vsAnchor">31</a>
       <span id="vs31">And Je&acute;hu himself did not take care to walk in the law of Jehovah the God of Israel with all his heart. He did not turn aside from the sins of Jer&middot;o&middot;bo&acute;am with which he caused Israel to sin.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk32" class="vsAnchor">32</a>
       <span id="vs32">In those days Jehovah started to cut off Israel piece by piece; and Haz&acute;a&middot;el kept striking them in all the territory of Israel,</span> <a name="bk33" class="vsAnchor">33</a>
       <span id="vs33">from the Jordan toward the rising of the sun, all the land of Gil&acute;e&middot;ad, the Gad&acute;ites and the Reu&acute;ben&middot;ites and the Ma&middot;nas&acute;sites, from A&middot;ro&acute;er, which is by the torrent valley of Ar&acute;non, even Gil&acute;e&middot;ad and Ba&acute;shan.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk34" class="vsAnchor">34</a>
       <span id="vs34">And the rest of the affairs of Je&acute;hu and all that he did and all his mightiness, are they not written in the book of the affairs of the days of the kings of Israel?</span> <a name="bk35" class="vsAnchor">35</a>
       <span id="vs35">Finally Je&acute;hu lay down with his forefathers, and they buried him in Sa&middot;mar&acute;i&middot;a; and Je&middot;ho&acute;a&middot;haz his son began to reign in place of him.</span> <a name="bk36" class="vsAnchor">36</a>
       <span id="vs36">And the days that Je&acute;hu had reigned over Israel were twenty-eight years in Sa&middot;mar&acute;i&middot;a.</span>
</p>
</form>

