<h1>Online Bible: New World Translation of the Holy Scriptures</h1>
</noscript>
<p class="title">2 Kings 25:1-30</p>
<form class="formtext">
<input type="hidden" name="chapterCount" value="25">
<input type="hidden" name="verseCount" value="30">
<p><a name="bk1" class="vsAnchor">1</a>
       <span id="vs1">And it came about in the ninth year of his being king, in the tenth month on the tenth day of the month, that Neb&middot;u&middot;chad&middot;nez&acute;zar the king of Babylon came, yes, he and all his military force, against Jerusalem and began camping against it and building against it a siege wall all around.</span> <a name="bk2" class="vsAnchor">2</a>
       <span id="vs2">And the city came to be under siege until the eleventh year of King Zed&middot;e&middot;ki&acute;ah.</span> <a name="bk3" class="vsAnchor">3</a>
       <span id="vs3">On the ninth day of the [fourth] month the famine was severe in the city, and there proved to be no bread for the people of the land.</span> <a name="bk4" class="vsAnchor">4</a>
       <span id="vs4">And the city got to be breached, and all the men of war [fled] by night by the way of the gate between the double wall that is by the king’s garden, while the Chal&middot;de&acute;ans were all around against the city; and [the king] began to go in the direction of the Ar&acute;a&middot;bah.</span> <a name="bk5" class="vsAnchor">5</a>
       <span id="vs5">And a military force of Chal&middot;de&acute;ans went chasing after the king, and they got to overtake him in the desert plains of Jer&acute;i&middot;cho; and all his own military force was scattered from his side.</span> <a name="bk6" class="vsAnchor">6</a>
       <span id="vs6">Then they seized the king and brought him up to the king of Babylon at Rib&acute;lah, that they might pronounce a judicial decision upon him.</span> <a name="bk7" class="vsAnchor">7</a>
       <span id="vs7">And Zed&middot;e&middot;ki&acute;ah’s sons they slaughtered before his eyes, and Zed&middot;e&middot;ki&acute;ah’s eyes he blinded, after which he bound him with copper fetters and brought him to Babylon.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk8" class="vsAnchor">8</a>
       <span id="vs8">And in the fifth month on the seventh [day] of the month, that is to say, the nineteenth year of King Neb&middot;u&middot;chad&middot;nez&acute;zar the king of Babylon, Neb&middot;u&acute;zar&middot;ad&acute;an the chief of the bodyguard, the servant of the king of Babylon, came to Jerusalem.</span> <a name="bk9" class="vsAnchor">9</a>
       <span id="vs9">And he proceeded to burn the house of Jehovah and the king’s house and all the houses of Jerusalem; and the house of every great man he burned with fire.</span> <a name="bk10" class="vsAnchor">10</a>
       <span id="vs10">And the walls of Jerusalem, all around, the entire military force of Chal&middot;de&acute;ans that were with the chief of the bodyguard pulled down.</span> <a name="bk11" class="vsAnchor">11</a>
       <span id="vs11">And the rest of the people that were left behind in the city and the deserters that had gone over to the king of Babylon and the rest of the crowd Neb&middot;u&acute;zar&middot;ad&acute;an the chief of the bodyguard took into exile.</span> <a name="bk12" class="vsAnchor">12</a>
       <span id="vs12">And some of the lowly people of the land the chief of the bodyguard let remain as vinedressers and compulsory laborers.</span> <a name="bk13" class="vsAnchor">13</a>
       <span id="vs13">And the pillars of copper that were in the house of Jehovah, and the carriages and the copper sea that were in the house of Jehovah, the Chal&middot;de&acute;ans broke in pieces and went carrying the copper of them to Babylon.</span> <a name="bk14" class="vsAnchor">14</a>
       <span id="vs14">And the cans and the shovels and the extinguishers and the cups and all the utensils of copper with which they used to minister they took.</span> <a name="bk15" class="vsAnchor">15</a>
       <span id="vs15">And the chief of the bodyguard took the fire holders and the bowls that were of genuine gold and those that were of genuine silver.</span> <a name="bk16" class="vsAnchor">16</a>
       <span id="vs16">As for the two pillars, the one sea and the carriages that Sol&acute;o&middot;mon had made for the house of Jehovah, there happened to be no way to tell the weight of the copper of all these utensils.</span> <a name="bk17" class="vsAnchor">17</a>
       <span id="vs17">Eighteen cubits was the height of each pillar, and the capital upon it was of copper; and the height of the capital was three cubits; and the network and the pomegranates all around upon the capital, the whole of it, was copper; and the second pillar had the same as these upon the network.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk18" class="vsAnchor">18</a>
       <span id="vs18">Furthermore, the chief of the bodyguard took Se&middot;rai&acute;ah the chief priest and Zeph&middot;a&middot;ni&acute;ah the second priest and three doorkeepers;</span> <a name="bk19" class="vsAnchor">19</a>
       <span id="vs19">and from the city he took one court official that had a command over the men of war, and five men from those having access to the king that were found in the city; and the secretary of the chief of the army, the one mustering the people of the land, and sixty men of the people of the land that were to be found in the city;</span> <a name="bk20" class="vsAnchor">20</a>
       <span id="vs20">and Neb&middot;u&acute;zar&middot;ad&acute;an the chief of the bodyguard then took them and conducted them to the king of Babylon at Rib&acute;lah.</span> <a name="bk21" class="vsAnchor">21</a>
       <span id="vs21">And the king of Babylon proceeded to strike them down and put them to death at Rib&acute;lah in the land of Ha&acute;math. Thus Judah went into exile from off its soil.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk22" class="vsAnchor">22</a>
       <span id="vs22">As for the people left behind in the land of Judah, whom Neb&middot;u&middot;chad&middot;nez&acute;zar the king of Babylon had left behind, he now appointed over them Ged&middot;a&middot;li&acute;ah the son of A&middot;hi&acute;kam the son of Sha&acute;phan.</span> <a name="bk23" class="vsAnchor">23</a>
       <span id="vs23">When all the chiefs of the military forces, they and their men, heard that the king of Babylon had appointed Ged&middot;a&middot;li&acute;ah, they immediately came to Ged&middot;a&middot;li&acute;ah at Miz&acute;pah, that is, Ish&acute;ma&middot;el the son of Neth&middot;a&middot;ni&acute;ah and Jo&middot;ha&acute;nan the son of Ka&middot;re&acute;ah and Se&middot;rai&acute;ah the son of Tan&middot;hu&acute;meth the Ne&middot;toph&acute;a&middot;thite and Ja&middot;az&middot;a&middot;ni&acute;ah the son of the Ma&middot;ac&acute;a&middot;thite, they and their men.</span> <a name="bk24" class="vsAnchor">24</a>
       <span id="vs24">Then Ged&middot;a&middot;li&acute;ah swore to them and their men and said to them: “Do not be afraid of [being] servants to the Chal&middot;de&acute;ans. Dwell in the land and serve the king of Babylon, and it will go well with <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span>.”</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk25" class="vsAnchor">25</a>
       <span id="vs25">And it came about in the seventh month that Ish&acute;ma&middot;el the son of Neth&middot;a&middot;ni&acute;ah the son of E&middot;lish&acute;a&middot;ma of the royal offspring came, and also ten men with him, and they got to strike down Ged&middot;a&middot;li&acute;ah, so that he died, and also the Jews and the Chal&middot;de&acute;ans that happened to be with him in Miz&acute;pah.</span> <a name="bk26" class="vsAnchor">26</a>
       <span id="vs26">After that all the people, from small to great, and the chiefs of the military forces rose up and came into Egypt; for they had become afraid because of the Chal&middot;de&acute;ans.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk27" class="vsAnchor">27</a>
       <span id="vs27">And it came about in the thirty-seventh year of the exile of Je&middot;hoi&acute;a&middot;chin the king of Judah, in the twelfth month, on the twenty-seventh day of the month, that E&acute;vil-mer&acute;o&middot;dach the king of Babylon, in the year of his becoming king, raised up the head of Je&middot;hoi&acute;a&middot;chin the king of Judah out of the house of detention;</span> <a name="bk28" class="vsAnchor">28</a>
       <span id="vs28">and he began to speak good things with him, and then put his throne higher than the thrones of the kings that were with him in Babylon.</span> <a name="bk29" class="vsAnchor">29</a>
       <span id="vs29">And he took off his prison garments; and he ate bread constantly before him all the days of his life.</span> <a name="bk30" class="vsAnchor">30</a>
       <span id="vs30">As for his allowance, an allowance was constantly given him from the king, daily as due, all the days of his life.</span>
</p>
</form>

